data.name: SystemPointer
desc: specifies the shape of a mouse pointer.

items.name: ARROW
lines: specifies the normal arrow-like mouse pointer.

items.name: INVISIBLE
lines: specifies an invisible mouse pointer.

items.name: WAIT
lines: specifies a waiting symbol as a mouse pointer (for example hourglass).

items.name: TEXT
lines: specifies a mouse pointer for text (cursor-like).

items.name: HELP
lines: specifies a mouse pointer for on-line help.

items.name: CROSS
lines: specifies a cross as a mouse pointer.

items.name: MOVE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes movement.

items.name: NSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes resizing for a top border.

items.name: SSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes resizing for a bottom border.

items.name: WSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes resizing for a left border.

items.name: ESIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes resizing for a right border.

items.name: NWSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes resizing for the top-left corner.

items.name: NESIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes resizing for the top-right corner.

items.name: SWSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes resizing for the bottom-left corner.

items.name: SESIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes resizing for the bottom-right corner.

items.name: WINDOW_NSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes window resizing for a top border.

items.name: WINDOW_SSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes window resizing for a bottom border.

items.name: WINDOW_WSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes window resizing for a left border.

items.name: WINDOW_ESIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes window resizing for a right border.

items.name: WINDOW_NWSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes window resizing for the top-left corner.

items.name: WINDOW_NESIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes window resizing for the top-right corner.

items.name: WINDOW_SWSIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes window resizing for the bottom-left corner.

items.name: WINDOW_SESIZE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes window resizing for the bottom-right corner.

items.name: HSPLIT
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes horizontal splitting.

items.name: VSPLIT
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes vertical splitting.

items.name: HSIZEBAR
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes horizontal resizing.

items.name: VSIZEBAR
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes vertical resizing.

items.name: HAND
lines: specifies a hand symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: REFHAND
lines: specifies a pointing hand symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: PEN
lines: specifies a pen symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: MAGNIFY
lines: specifies a magnify symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: FILL
lines: specifies a fill symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: ROTATE
lines: specifies a rotate symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: HSHEAR
lines: specifies a horizontal shear symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: VSHEAR
lines: specifies a vertical shear symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: MIRROR
lines: specifies a mirror symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: CROOK
lines: specifies a crook symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: CROP
lines: specifies a crop symbol as mouse pointer.

items.name: MOVEPOINT
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes moving a point.

items.name: MOVEBEZIERWEIGHT
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes moving a Bezier weight.

items.name: MOVEDATA
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes moving data.

items.name: COPYDATA
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes copying data.

items.name: LINKDATA
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes linking data.

items.name: MOVEDATALINK
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes moving a data link.

items.name: COPYDATALINK
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes copying a data link.

items.name: MOVEFILE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes moving a file.

items.name: COPYFILE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes copying a file.

items.name: LINKFILE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes linking a file.

items.name: MOVEFILELINK
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes moving a file link.

items.name: COPYFILELINK
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes copying a file link.

items.name: MOVEFILES
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes moving multiple files.

items.name: COPYFILES
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes copying multiple files.

items.name: NOTALLOWED
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes \"not allowed\".

items.name: DRAW_LINE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing a line.

items.name: DRAW_RECT
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing a rectangle.

items.name: DRAW_POLYGON
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing a polygon.

items.name: DRAW_BEZIER
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing a Bezier.

items.name: DRAW_ARC
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing an arc.

items.name: DRAW_PIE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing a pie.

items.name: DRAW_CIRCLECUT
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing a circle cut.

items.name: DRAW_ELLIPSE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing an ellipse.

items.name: DRAW_FREEHAND
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing free handed.

items.name: DRAW_CONNECT
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing a connector.

items.name: DRAW_TEXT
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing text.

items.name: DRAW_CAPTION
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes drawing a text caption.

items.name: CHART
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes a chart.

items.name: DETECTIVE
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes a detective.

items.name: PIVOT_COL
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes a pivot column.

items.name: PIVOT_ROW
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes a pivot row.

items.name: PIVOT_FIELD
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes a pivot field.

items.name: CHAIN
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes a chain.

items.name: CHAIN_NOTALLOWED
lines: specifies a mouse pointer which symbolizes \"chaining not allowed\".
